{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-22T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Earth Day didn't knock gently. It kicked the door wide open. In 1970, oil‑soaked beaches, burning rivers, and toxic air mobilized millions into street protests. When looking away was no longer an option, conservation was forced onto political agendas, sparking landmark environmental laws and flipping planet‑care from fringe concern to global priority. Every April 22, over 190 countries pause, reflect, and reassess.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_EN-US1627168155_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_EN-US1627168155_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The power of protest","Title":"Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve in Tartu County, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/58.466962,26.199884/6?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=58.466962,26.199884;S9;Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve, Tartu County, Estonia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Earth+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260422_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia"},"Ssd":"20260422","Name":"TartuEstonia","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1627168155","FullDateString":"Apr 22, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring arrives with a small, spiky ambassador: the European hedgehog, spotted here in France. Part cuddle, part survival gear, this tiny forager is mostly nocturnal and usually solitary, guided mainly by smell and sound. Its job description is simple: roam, sniff through leaf litter, and vacuum up invertebrates like worms, beetles, slugs, and caterpillars—the kind of snacks that keep ecosystems running and gardeners smiling. When danger shows up, it doesn't negotiate or flee. It curls into a tight ball and lets its spines do the talking.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_EN-US1312133826_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_EN-US1312133826_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spring's prickly patrol","Title":"European hedgehog, France","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Its 5,000-7,000 spines are stiff, hollow hairs made of keratin, not true quills like a porcupine's.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=european+hedgehog&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260421_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog"},"Ssd":"20260421","Name":"SpringHedgehog","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1312133826","FullDateString":"Apr 21, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"National Park Week is your cue to trade routine for trail dust. It's a nine-day celebration running April 18–26, highlighting more than 400 places across the National Park System that preserve natural and cultural heritage while creating unforgettable outdoor experiences. From coastlines and forests to vast desert landscapes, these protected sites invite exploration, reflection, and wonder.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_EN-US1031978429_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_EN-US1031978429_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The adventure doesn't end at sundown","Title":"Sunset in Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah","Copyright":"© Jason Hatfield/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.213604,-109.902534/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.213604,-109.902534;S9;Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=National+Park+Week&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260420_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva"},"Ssd":"20260420","Name":"SunsetKiva","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1031978429","FullDateString":"Apr 20, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"National Library Week kicks off today as libraries across the United States celebrate the power of free access to knowledge—and for younger generations, that availability can be life-shaping. Created by the American Library Association, it highlights how libraries support literacy, curiosity, and learning at every age, especially in childhood, when reading habits first take root.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LibraryWeek_EN-US0888768835_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LibraryWeek_EN-US0888768835_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Stories start here","Title":"Books in the children's section of The New York Public Library, New York","Copyright":"© Ken Welsh/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"National Library Week 2026, themed 'Find Your Joy,' invites people of all ages to discover what brings them joy at their local library.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260419_LibraryWeek\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=National+Library+Week&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260419_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260419_LibraryWeek"},"Ssd":"20260419","Name":"LibraryWeek","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0888768835","FullDateString":"Apr 19, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, on World Heritage Day, attention turns to places that tell humanity's shared story—protected for their exceptional cultural or natural value. One of them rises from volcanic stone on Easter Island, Chile. At Rano Raraku, the slopes of an extinct volcano became the workshop where nearly all of the island's famous moai were carved. The image captures this remarkable quarry, where half-finished figures emerge from the rock, frozen mid-creation.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MaoiStatues_EN-US0752877903_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MaoiStatues_EN-US0752877903_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"The silence of unfinished giants","Title":"Moai statue quarry, Rano Raraku, Easter Island, Chile","Copyright":"© Gavin Hellier/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-27.127001,-109.292099/10?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-27.127001,-109.292099;S9;Rano Raraku, Easter Island, Chile&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260418_MaoiStatues\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Heritage+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260418_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260418_MaoiStatues"},"Ssd":"20260418","Name":"MaoiStatues","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0752877903","FullDateString":"Apr 18, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"On April 17, International Bat Appreciation Day flips its cape to the planet's night shift: bats. With more than 1,400 species on every continent except Antarctica, these winged mammals keep ecosystems balanced. They've been on Earth for over 50 million years, and only three species are true vampires. Found only in the Americas, these bats feed on blood, while the rest survive on insects, fruit, nectar, or pollen. In Texas, Bracken Cave can host up to 20 million Mexican free-tailed bats in summer. Many gulp crop pests, cutting pesticide use; others pollinate wild agaves and disperse seeds that help forests rebound.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_EN-US0502464388_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_EN-US0502464388_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bat signal: ON","Title":"Grey-headed flying fox carrying her pup, Yarra Bend Park, Australia","Copyright":"© Doug Gimesy/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-37.798065,145.012222/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-37.798065,145.012222;S9;Yarra Bend Park, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bats&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260417_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom"},"Ssd":"20260417","Name":"FlyingFoxMom","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0502464388","FullDateString":"Apr 17, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each spring, Washington's Skagit Valley transforms into a patchwork of color as the Skagit Valley Tulip Festival celebrates the arrival of bloom season. Throughout April, visitors can explore tulip gardens and farmland lined with vibrant rows of flowers, all framed by mountain views.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_EN-US8944602365_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_EN-US8944602365_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Petal parade","Title":"Skagit Valley Tulip Fields, Washington","Copyright":"© Alan Majchrowicz/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/48.5,-122.033/7?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=48.5,-122.033;S9;Skagit Valley, Washington&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Skagit+Valley+Washington&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260416_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips"},"Ssd":"20260416","Name":"SkagitTulips","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"8944602365","FullDateString":"Apr 16, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ships leaving Lisbon once passed a small stone tower before meeting the wide Atlantic. That tower, standing on the bank of the Tagus River, served as both a guardian and a farewell. Say hello to Belém Tower—a fortress that watched Portugal sail into the Age of Exploration.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_EN-US2528466391_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_EN-US2528466391_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"History anchored in stone","Title":"Belém Tower on the bank of the Tagus River, Lisbon, Portugal","Copyright":"© f9photos/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.69165,-9.215943/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.69165,-9.215943;S9;Belém Tower, Lisbon, Portugal&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Belem+Tower&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260429_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank"},"Ssd":"20260429","Name":"BelemTowerBank","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"2528466391","FullDateString":"Apr 29, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The spectacled bear, also known as the Andean bear, is the only South American bear of the Ursidae family. Inhabiting the northern and central Andes Mountains, it dwells primarily in forested areas and feeds mainly on shoots and fruit. Pale markings around the eyes often resemble eyeglasses, or 'spectacles,' giving the species its distinctive name.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-US2465945308_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-US2465945308_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spectacles in the wild","Title":"Spectacled bear resting in tree, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Each spectacled bear has unique facial markings, which scientists use to identify and track individuals in the wild.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Spectacled+bear&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260428_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear"},"Ssd":"20260428","Name":"AndeanBear","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"2465945308","FullDateString":"Apr 28, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Designed by architect Giuseppe Mengoni and completed in 1877, the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II in Milan, Italy, is one of the world's oldest and most famous shopping arcades. Located between Piazza del Duomo and Piazza della Scala, it features a stunning glass-and-iron roof and an elegant, octagonal layout. Affectionately known as 'Milan's living room,' the Galleria is home to high-end boutiques, historic cafés such as Caffè Biffi and Camparino in Galleria, and renowned restaurants.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-US2432086382_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-US2432086382_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Glass with class","Title":"The glass dome of Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy","Copyright":"© PhillipMinnis/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/45.466179,9.18992/11?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=45.466179,9.18992;S9;Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galleria+Vittorio+Emanuele+II+Milan+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260427_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria"},"Ssd":"20260427","Name":"MilanGalleria","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"2432086382","FullDateString":"Apr 27, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring brings apple trees to life with clouds of soft pink blossoms. Their delicate petals brighten orchards and hillsides, standing out against clear blue skies as the season shifts from winter toward warmer days. These blooms attract pollinators such as bees and butterflies, helping fruit trees produce the apples that will grow later in the year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-US2396192691_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-US2396192691_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bloom boom","Title":"Pink apple blossoms, Avila Beach, California","Copyright":"© Mimi Ditchie Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/35.177404,-120.733528/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=35.177404,-120.733528;S9;Avila Beach, California&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=apple+tree&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260426_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260426","Name":"AppleBlossoms","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"2396192691","FullDateString":"Apr 26, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Penguins usually bring Antarctica to mind, but these endearing flightless seabirds don't always follow the ice. On World Penguin Day, the Galápagos penguins pictured here offer a vivid counterpoint. Found only in the Galápagos Islands—a volcanic archipelago about 600 miles off Ecuador's coast—this species lives farther north than any other penguin. Cool, nutrient‑rich ocean currents make this equatorial habitat possible by supplying food and keeping surrounding waters within survivable temperatures. Compact and agile, these birds spend much of the day in the water to stay cool.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_EN-US2287809863_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_EN-US2287809863_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Breaking the penguin rules","Title":"Galápagos penguins swimming, Galápagos Islands, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Henley Spiers/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-0.859397,-91.215904/8?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-0.859397,-91.215904;S9;Galápagos Islands, Ecuador&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Penguin+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260425_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins"},"Ssd":"20260425","Name":"GalapagosPenguins","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"2287809863","FullDateString":"Apr 25, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Arbor Day celebrates the quiet power of trees—the way they steady ecosystems, shelter wildlife, cool cities, and shape the environments we rely on every day. Observed in the United States on the last Friday in April, the day encourages communities here—and in many other countries, where dates vary according to growing season—to plant, protect, and care for forests of every kind, from neighborhood canopies to iconic wildlands.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_EN-US2059787604_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_EN-US2059787604_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A tribute to trees","Title":"Forest hammock of slash pine and saw palmetto, Everglades National Park, Florida","Copyright":"© Mary Liz Austin/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/25.400611,-80.658833/6?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=25.400611,-80.658833;S9;Everglades National Park, Florida&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Arbor+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260424_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine"},"Ssd":"20260424","Name":"SlashPine","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"2059787604","FullDateString":"Apr 24, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each April 23, the curtain rises on the life and legacy of William Shakespeare, a playwright whose words still command the world's literary stage. Shakespeare Day commemorates the anniversary of his death in 1616 and the traditionally accepted date of his birth in 1564—a symbolic pairing that honors a writer whose works reshaped English literature. From the psychological depths of 'Hamlet' to the enduring romance of 'Romeo and Juliet,' his language continues to echo through classrooms, theaters, and everyday speech. His plays have been performed in numerous languages worldwide.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HathawayCottage_EN-US1795877015_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HathawayCottage_EN-US1795877015_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"A cottage full of stories","Title":"Anne Hathaway's cottage and garden, Stratford-upon-Avon, England","Copyright":"© David Steele/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.190984,-1.732059/9?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.190984,-1.732059;S9;Anne Hathaway's cottage, Stratford-upon-Avon, England&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_t